    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2843188718" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2843188718" />
    <a title="S.P. Aruna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58833010-s-p-aruna"><img alt="S.P. Aruna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1471747692p2/58833010.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2843188718?book_show_action=true">Jun 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="S.P. Aruna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="S.P. Aruna" href="/user/show/58833010-s-p-aruna">S.P. Aruna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58833010-s-p-aruna?shelf=thriller-mystery">thriller-mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2843188718" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12632689868970628555">My first book from this author, and I&apos;m now convinced that Ms Cornwell reigns supreme as a crime fiction writer. I&apos;m hooked! I&apos;ll be reading as much as I can of her works.<br/><br/>Her series protagonist, Kay Scarpetta, a forensic pathologist, seems as genuine as they come. The novel&apos;s prose is written with a level of sophistication above the norm for the genre, and the technical details are as well researched as the descriptions found in the books by Thomas Harris <br/><br/>Logically enough, I started with the fir</span>
  <span id="freeText12632689868970628555" style="display:none">My first book from this author, and I'm now convinced that Ms Cornwell reigns supreme as a crime fiction writer. I'm hooked! I'll be reading as much as I can of her works.<br /><br />Her series protagonist, Kay Scarpetta, a forensic pathologist, seems as genuine as they come. The novel's prose is written with a level of sophistication above the norm for the genre, and the technical details are as well researched as the descriptions found in the books by Thomas Harris <br /><br />Logically enough, I started with the first of the series. The plot is one we've seen over and over, a brutal serial killer, but the way he is caught is a mind-bender that you won't see in any other similar story.<br /><br />While the involvement of a Chief Medical Examiner in a crime investigation is slightly stretched, it is not totally out of bounds. The author focuses on real world dialogue rather than witty, smart-alec remarks, and this adds an earthy, graphic depth to the story.<br /><br />If you love mysteries and crime fiction, this author's books are HIGHLY recommended.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12632689868970628555" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

